ce:section.ce:para:
Quantitative real-time PCR (qPCR) was performed on ABI ViiA 7™ real-time PCR system (Applied Biosystems, Carlsbad, CA, USA) with SYBR Premix Ex TaqTM II (Perfect Real Time, Takara, Dalian, China). Total RNAs of zebrafish larvae were extracted using the RNAisoPlus (Takara, Dalian, China) and the first-strand cDNAs were synthesized from 1 μg of the total mRNAs using PrimeScript™ RT reagent kit with gDNA eraser (Takara, Dalian, China) according to the standard protocol. qPCR was performed with the running program as the follows: firstly an incubation of 95 ℃ for 2 min, and then 40 cycles of 95 ℃ for 10 s, 60 ℃ for 30 s, and 72 ℃ for 10 s. Primer pairs were designed with the software Beacon Designer 8.14 (

                        Table 1
                        ) and ef1α was used as the internal control to normalize the relative mRNA levels. Four independent biological replicates were carried out for each treatment and 2-ΔΔCt method was employed for detecting the mRNA expression levels.
